Wed May 22 15:06:14 MEST 2002 - tom@suse.de

- This is a new version for Rel.8.1 where SaX is used to write the XF86Config
  on the whole. Consequently there are some new Requirements.
  o  Do not support Xfree 3 any more. (SaX can't do it).
        Don't distinguish XFree3 from XFree4.
  o  Do not write rc.sax sections on the whole (only partly update them).
        Therefore the functions writing the different rc.sax sections must not
        write static data (as was convenient up to now to *create* the sections
  o  Remove option to have "manual" font paths (rely on SaX entirely).
  o  Remove any functionality that is not related to mouse, keyboard or
     language (writing).

  All other functionality was good only for *creating* the XF86Config file
  which is now done by SaX.

  Now this agent is no longer capable of *creating* a fullsize XF68Config file.
  Instead of this it can now do a true update of some sections, i.e. pass only
  that information to isax that has changed in some way (no static section
  data anymore).

  TODO:
  The keyboard functionality has to be redone in the future due to a new
  method of information gaining to be used by the keyboard module.

